Paul's face drops. He is taken aback. \nPaul:"What do you mean?". He signals at the waitress, "Brenda, two espressos please!" \n\nAs the both of you sit down on the opposite chairs, Paul starts talking, "Are you leaving me?"\n\n[["I am joining the Loving Vincent team, starting next month"]]\n[[" Of course not, but I am considering leaving the city to join the Loving Vincent team!"]]\n[["I do not want to leave you but I have to go to Poland to be an artist for Loving Vincent"]]
George seems a little confused. \n\nAs the waitress passes by, he shouts out, "Hey Brenda! Can we have two espressos please?" George then turns towards you and looks at you, "what do you mean?"\n\nYou grab his hand and blurt out, "You and I, our first exhibition. It is finally happening...and that too during the Atlanta Arts festival."\n\nGeorge looks down at the floor. His eyebrows furrowed- as if he is remembering something. He asks, "The festival? Isn't it in a couple of weeks?"\n\n[["Yes it is right in the beginning of next month!"|"Yes it is right in the begining of next month!"]]\n[["How does it matter? I have enough new works for an exhibition, don't worry!"]]\n[["Yes it is just around the corner! We have so much to do and so little time!"]]\n
It must be an incoming call, but nothing can divert your attention at this moment. You continue with all your questions and start writing down the details of the logistics on your sketchbook, as Mr Leland continues speaking. You don't even notice when the beeping finally stops. \n\nAfter about 40 minutes, when the converation finally ends, you notice that a new [[message]] had arrived while you were talking on the phone. It is George.

<p class="email">\s\n<div class="image2">\n[>img[vincent]]\n</div>\s\nDear George,\n\nWe are pleased to let you know that after careful review of your portfolio pieces, we have decided to extend you the offer of joining our team. \n\nThis is the first fully painted feature film in the world, directed by Polish painter and director Dorota Kobiela and Hugh Welchman (Oscar winner for producing "Peter and the Wolf"). The film is produced by Oscar-winning Studios Breakthru Films and Trademark Films.\n\nYou are hereby invited to our main studio in Gdansk, Poland for 3-days of audition starting on the 8th of next month. Under supervision you will paint and animate part of a shot to see if you have an aptitude for this, and to see if you enjoy it. If you do well in this test you will be invited to join an intensive training course.\n\nThis will be an intensive 180 hour course to learn to paint in the style of Van Gogh, and to bring those paintings to animated life. Judging by your skills, we feel confident that you will be selected to animate shots on our movie. Finally, you will be invited to join our team for the final 6 months of production, and become part of making film history!\n\nPlease confirm your acceptance by replying to this email.\n\nBest Wishes,\nThe Loving Vincent team\n</p>\n<<if $rand is 1>>\s\n[[later in the day]]\n<<else>>\s\n[[text Paul]]\n<<endif>>
